<item>
 <title>Postdoctoral research associate, Functional analysis of candidate disease resistance genes</title>
 <link>https://legacy.vectorbase.org/jobpostings/postdoctoral-research-associate-functional-analysis-candidate-disease-resistance-genes</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot; property=&quot;content:encoded&quot;&gt;&lt;p align=&quot;justify&quot;&gt;Candidate will work in the laboratory of &lt;a href=&quot;https://ib.oregonstate.edu/faculty/blouinm/Blouin-Michael&quot;&gt;Dr. Michael Blouin&lt;/a&gt; to perform  
work on new NIH grant anticipated in Spring of 2019. The aim of this  
project is to identify genes in the snail, &lt;em&gt;Biomphalaria glabrata&lt;/em., that  
convey resistance to &lt;em&gt;Schistosoma mansoni&lt;/em&gt;, a major parasite of humans  
that is transmitted by this snail host  
&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Schistosomiasis&quot;&gt;(https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Schistosomiasis)&lt;/a&gt;. We have mapped major  
QTL that control infection risk in laboratory populations of snails,  
and have annotated nearby candidate genes. The goal for this position  
is to functionally assess candidate genes for their role in  
resistance. The main approach will be gene knockdowns using RNAi, but  
may include CRISPR or other techniques. Once causal gene(s) are  
identified, work will focus on their mechanisms of action, including  
how they interact with parasite-derived molecules. The long-term goal  
of this research is to find ways to block transmission of  
schistosomiasis via interference with the snail host. &lt;em&gt;Biomphalaria&lt;/em&gt; and  
&lt;em&gt;Schistosoma&lt;/em&gt; form a well-studied, model host-parasite system with  
numerous available molecular and genomic resources and established  
laboratory protocols. We are looking for a creative individual who  
will also develop their own ideas using this system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/br&gt;
   Corvallis, Oregon, is a medium-sized city, set in a beautiful area  
of the Pacific Northwest.  It is well known for its high quality of  
life that includes a safe, progressive and intellectually vibrant  
community, and ready access to many outdoor recreational activities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/br&gt;

   Questions? Email Mike at blouinm@oregonstate.edu.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/br&gt;

Official position description:  
&lt;a href=&quot;https://jobs.oregonstate.edu/postings/70041/print_preview&quot;&gt;https://jobs.oregonstate.edu/postings/70041/print_preview&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/br&gt;

To apply: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jobs.oregonstate.edu/postings/69874&quot;&gt;https://jobs.oregonstate.edu/postings/69874&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/br&gt;


